":null,\"session_id\":\"c77d786c-a861-49d7-8b43-8b230b08cc6a\",\"uuid\":\"1edd31f0-6b99-4809-9f7d-b8508a935253\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T17:14:10.120Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"success\":true,\"commandName\":\"idea-0c0540c6-extract-dispatch-pipeline-into\"}}\n    14→[2026-03-18T17:14:10.216Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\\n\\n## REQUIREMENT\\n\\n# Extract dispatch pipeline into composable stages\\n\\n## Metadata\\n- **Category**: maintenance\\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\\n- **Generated**: 3/17/2026, 11:16:21 PM\\n\\n## Description\\ndispatchToWorker conflates four distinct concerns into one 140-line method: token acquisition (OAuth/fallback), persona resolution with credential decryption, prompt assembly with model profile routing, and the actual WebSocket send. Refactor into a pipeline of typed stages (ResolveToken -> ResolvePersona -> AssemblePayload -> Send) where each stage is independently testable and replaceable.\\n\\n## Reasoning\\nThis method is the single highest-risk function in the system � it touches secrets, crypto, external auth, DB reads, and network I/O. Yet it cannot be unit tested without mocking everything because the concerns are interleaved. Decomposition would make each stage independently verifiable and allow new provider integrations without touching dispatch logic.\\n\\n\\n## Recommended Skills\\n\\n- **compact-ui-design**: Use `.claude/skills/compact-ui-design.md` for high-quality UI design references and patterns\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\\n\\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\\n\\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\\n\\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\\n\\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \\\"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\\\")\\n\\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\\n\\nBegin implementation now.\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"c77d786c-a861-49d7-8b43-8b230b08cc6a\",\"uuid\":\"ac48fb2f-08ae-4e61-84d8-42bfc8f76ae2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T17:14:10.119Z\",\"isSynthetic\":true}\n    15→[2026-03-18T17:14:13.260Z] [STDOUT] {\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01QTx6agXdgf2y1w5fTzJG73\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me start by understanding the current `dispatchToWorker` method in the dispatcher module, and then plan the refactoring into composable pipeline stages.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":688,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":18337,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":688},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"c77d786c-a861-49d7-8b43-8b230b08cc6a\",\"uuid\":\"f8f17293-c7c8-45a0-8282-9a08f26fe47a\"}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3bcc19da-3c07-4438-8ba2-7e4a234fa1f7","uuid":"58d717f7-7c73-4ed7-9b86-8fabcd04aeb1","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:45:05.428Z","tool_use_result"